---

<CoursePage
  title="hidden history"
  theme="classified"
  identityLabel="evidence desk // clearance required"
  tagline="coverups, conspiracies, hoaxes, and the evidence that sorts them out."
  intro="Some of the wildest government stories are true. Plenty aren't. We open the files, check where every claim came from, and learn when the honest answer is ‘we don't know.’ Watergate, MKUltra, COINTELPRO, UFOs, hoaxes—the fun is figuring out which box each one belongs in."
  units={units}
  resources={resources}
>
  <QuickTake
    slot="hook"
    id="hidden-history-opening-take"
    eyebrow="make the first call. then test it."
    question="A secret file contradicts the official story. What earns your belief first?"
    options={[
      { label: 'the document', response: 'Start with provenance: who made it, when, for whom, and whether the document is authentic. Real paper can still contain bad information.' },
      { label: 'a witness', response: 'A witness gives detail and perspective—not automatic truth. Check timing, incentives, memory, and independent corroboration.' },
      { label: 'the pattern', response: 'Patterns can reveal a system or expose our own pattern-hungry brains. Name what evidence would prove your pattern wrong before you trust it.' },
    ]}
  />

  <DailyDesk note="a claim, a file, and one way your brain may be messing with you.">
    <DailyCard label="verdict of the day" entries={verdicts} />
    <DailyCard label="declassified file of the day" entries={files} />
    <DailyCard label="trick of the week" entries={tricks} />
    <DailyCard label="argue this" entries={argueThis} />
  </DailyDesk>
</CoursePage>
